ANC leader Musalia Mudavadi toured Mombasa last Saturday to ratify a Luhya-Luo deal to capture the Nyali MP seat, the Star has learnt.Mudavadi was crowned Luhya spokesperson last year after a survey by the University of Nairobi lecturers.A week before his visit, the Nyali Abaluhya Association held a series of meetings to negotiate a deal. The meetings were chaired by chairman Clement Wasike.Mombasa Luo Council of Elders too held separate gatherings, crafting structures and a module of engagement. The Luhyas will give up the MP seat and get the Mkomani MCA slot and other seats to be identified. Simon Adalla, a Wiper candidate for the MP seat, was considered by Luo elders.